news.title: JK Cement commissions ₹500 crore, three MTPA plant in Bihar’s Buxar
news.para: JK Cement has inaugurated its first manufacturing plant in Buxar, Bihar, with a capacity of 3 million tonnes per year. The ₹500 crore facility is expected to slash logistics costs and accelerate deliveries to the Bihar market, reducing reliance on supplies from the Prayagraj plant in Uttar Pradesh.

news.title: Defaulters clear ₹27 lakh pending property tax ahead of auction in Bengaluru
news.para: Fear of property auctions prompted 14 defaulters in Bommanahalli to clear over Rs 27 lakh in pending dues before a Greater Bengaluru Authority auction. While this action recovered significant taxes, 36 properties remained unsold, with a re-auction planned for the outstanding arrears.

news.title: Kukatpally housing board plots, flats sold at record prices
news.para: Telangana Housing Board's auction in Kukatpally Housing Board saw land sold for a record 2.65 lakh per square yard. Open plots and flats were auctioned. The board earned 24.26 crore from the sale. This event highlights significant property value appreciation in the area.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad civic body to act against buildings lacking mandatory parking space
news.para: The Hubballi-Dharwad Municipal Corporation will demolish unauthorized basement structures in commercial complexes and apartment buildings to restore designated parking spaces. This action follows concerns about widespread violations of building norms, leading to severe traffic congestion and bottlenecks across the twin cities. The corporation will scrutinize completion certificates issued over the past five years.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body announces amnesty scheme till March 31
news.para: Pimpri Chinchwad Municipal Corporation has launched a property tax amnesty scheme offering a 90% waiver on penalties for defaulters. Taxpayers can clear their entire outstanding dues in a single payment between March 1 and March 31 to avail this benefit. This initiative aims to recover Rs 1,394 crore in arrears before the end of the financial year.

news.title: MCD recovers ₹11.69 crore in property tax from Delhi hotel
news.para: A Delhi hotel owner settled Rs 11.69 crore in overdue property tax after the Municipal Corporation of Delhi initiated action. The firm utilized the Sumpattikar Niptaan Yojana (SUNIYO) amnesty scheme, which waives interest and penalties before 2020-21. This scheme requires payment of the principal for current and five preceding years. The deadline is now February 28.

news.title: Delayed policy execution discourages investment: NAREDCO chairman
news.para: Delays in urban development policies and high stamp duty rates are impacting growth in Madhya Pradesh. NAREDCO Chairman Dr Niranjan Hiranandani highlighted issues with master planning and stamp duty structures. He suggested timely policy execution and reduced stamp duty could boost investment and employment. Regulatory clarity and updated city master plans are crucial for urban growth.

news.title: Compass to share real estate listings that have yet to hit the market broadly with Redfin
news.para: Compass and Redfin have entered into a three-year partnership, expanding Compass's off-market listings onto Redfin's platform. The collaboration could add more than 500,000 listings, broadening exposure for sellers as the spring housing market heats up. Rocket Mortgage will offer preferential pricing to Compass clients.

news.title: State Bank of India picks up 1.35 lakh sq ft office space in Navi Mumbai
news.para: The agreed rental stands at Rs 125.05 per sq ft per month, translating into a monthly outgo of over Rs 1.68 crore. The rent is inclusive of fit-outs, indicating that the space will be delivered in a ready-to-use format, reducing upfront capital expenditure and speeding up operational readiness.

news.title: HC orders Greater Bengaluru authority to re-inspect stormwater drains near apartment complexes
news.para: The High Court has ordered the GBA to re-inspect Gubbalala village lands after an expert committee found stormwater drain encroachments by two apartment complexes. The court directed the GBA to examine alternative drain alignments proposed by petitioners, ensuring water flow to Subramanyapura lake without disturbing neighbors.

news.title: Bedrooms for sale highlight the depths of Europe's housing crisis
news.para: Across Europe, affordability pressures push young buyers toward alternative paths. Co-living options, co-purchased mortgages for friends, and tenant-backed property stakes are reshaping access to homeownership. While these schemes ease entry in the short term, they also raise questions about risk, regulation, and long-term affordability as prices keep climbing.

news.title: Janus Living moves closer to US IPO with public filing
news.para: Janus Living, a real estate investment trust focused on senior housing communities, is pursuing a U.S. initial public offering. With assets concentrated in Florida and Texas, the company aims to unlock value across its senior housing portfolio. Bank of America Securities and J.P. Morgan are leading the offering, which plans to list on the New York Stock Exchange.

news.title: Jharkhand Housing Board issues notice to Mahendra Singh Dhoni over 'misuse' of residential plot
news.para: The Jharkhand State Housing Board has issued a notice to former Indian cricket captain Mahendra Singh Dhoni over allegations that a Ranchi residential plot was used for commercial purposes. The inquiry flagged a violation of rules, and a final notice has been issued. Non-compliance could lead to cancellation of the plot.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CM promises housing for all poor by 2029
news.para: Andhra Pradesh will provide housing for every poor family by 2029, with landless individuals receiving housing plots through expansive welfare housing programs. The government will drive agriculture forward through a five-pronged strategy, including enhanced financial support for farmers, backing for natural farming and food processing, and prioritized irrigation projects to boost productivity and rural livelihoods.

news.title: Rajasthan auctions 12 new sand mining plots despite HC order on replenishment studies
news.para: Rajasthan's mining department is moving ahead with auctions for new sand mining plots. This comes after the Rajasthan High Court cancelled previous gravel mining leases. The court had questioned the state's approach to natural replenishment of mined resources. Experts and industry representatives claim these new auctions disregard established norms and Supreme Court guidelines.

news.title: Vedaanta Senior Living invests ₹50 crore to develop senior living project in Tamil Nadu
news.para: Vedaanta Senior Living, in partnership with the Sameera Group, is developing Vedaanta Ananta in Chengalpattu, Tamil Nadu. The ₹50 crore investment will deliver 69 villas starting from ₹50 lakh, crafted to help seniors live independently with dignity.

news.title: SWAMIH Fund sanctions ₹115 crore for completion of Antriksh Valley project in Greater Noida West
news.para: The SWAMIH Investment Fund I has approved up to ₹115 crore for the stalled Antriksh Valley project in Greater Noida West. This funding will facilitate project completion, including a redesigned residential tower, after the new management cleared land dues and resolved homebuyer claims. The investment aims to restore homebuyer confidence in stalled housing projects.

news.title: Chandigarh administration forms new panel to decide future of rehabilitation colony houses
news.para: The newly formed panel was tasked with examining the present status of the properties, studying the legal framework governing them, and reviewing models adopted by other cities to address similar issues under rehabilitation schemes.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body collects ₹650 crore in property tax, 62% pay digitally
news.para: Navi Mumbai Municipal Corporation has collected Rs 650 crore in property tax this fiscal year, with 62% of payments made digitally. The civic body is intensifying efforts to meet its Rs 1,000 crore target by March 31, issuing notices and attaching properties of defaulters.

news.title: Action against illegal floor, office, colonies in Pataudi
news.para: As part of the drive, an illegal floor at Enkay Town Plaza in Palam Vihar was sealed following a complaint received through the CM Window grievance portal. Officials said the action targeted violations flagged through complaints and unauthorised plotting in peripheral urban areas.
